<HEADLINE>
<P>
JAMES B. MARINE; LONGTIME PUBLICIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 James B. Marine, a Los Angeles publicist who was twice elected president of 
the Western States Advertising Agencies Assn., has died.He was 69. 
</P>
<P>
 Marine died Wednesday in Los Angeles of complications from emphysema. 
</P>
<P>
 The former New York resident moved to Los Angeles in 1963 to become head of 
public relations for what was then the Bowes Co. He was named the company's 
president and CEO in 1971 and held those titles until the agency merged with 
Abert, Newhoff and Burr in 1990. 
</P>
<P>
 Marine was credited with creating the hummingbird logo for Marriott's Desert 
Springs Resort and Spa in Palm Desert. 
</P>
<P>
 In recent years, he was president of Brown, Keefe, Marine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
