<TEXT>
<P>
 TIES THAT BIND: Forging bonds with foreign towns has led to beautiful 
relationships for some Ventura County cities. . . . Thousand Oaks is holding an 
Oct. 16 concert to benefit Spitak, its Armenian sister city. Residents in 
Oxnard and Ocotlan, Mexico, regularly visit back and forth. And Fillmore is 
flirting with the notion of sisterhood with Osaka, Japan, after an Osaka 
delegation toured town last month. . . . But Santa Paula's been out of touch 
with its sister -- Obregon, Mexico -- even though a park is named after the 
Mexican town. "Maybe they have a park named after us," City Manager Arnold 
Dowdy pondered. 
</P>
<P>
 BATTLE LINES: Rep. Anthony C. Beilenson (D-Woodland Hills) may be in for the 
fight of his political career in November as he faces a strong anti-incumbent 
tide and well-financed GOP challenger Richard Sybert (A3). . . . The race has 
attracted national GOP luminaries eager to help Sybert oust the congressman 
from the district that includes Thousand Oaks. But Beilenson's campaign 
strategists say he's not your average incumbent. 
</P>
<P>
 PASSING MUSTER: Anything less than a C average may not be good enough to earn 
a high school diploma in Oxnard (B1). . . . School officials are considering 
the policy to beef up standards. They've already increased the number of 
credits required to graduate from 220 to 230. . . . Oak Park High has the 
county's highest credit requirement for graduation -- students need at least 
240. "If you have high expectations, kids reach those expectations," Principal 
Jeff Chancer said. 
</P>
<P>
 LIGHTNING STRIKES: Naturalist Gretel Ehrlich reads tonight at the Ventura 
Bookstore from her account of being struck by lightning. . . . In Ventura 
County, a computerized system that will help fire officials keep tabs on such 
occurrences goes on-line within six months. It will enable firefighters to sort 
emergency responses by category. "We'll be able to track more accurately the 
types of calls we get," county Fire Capt. Alex Sanchez said. Sister Cities 
</P>
<P>
 Four cities in Ventura County have sister-city relationships with towns in 
other countries, while Fillmore has been talking to Japanese officials about 
establishing such a tie. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks Spitak: Armenia 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard: Ocotlan: Mexico 
</P>
<P>
 Camarillo: Autlan: Mexico 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Paula: Obregon, Mexico 
</P>
<P>
 Fillmore: Osaka, Japan 
</P>
