<HEADLINE>
<P>
A LOOK AT LAWYERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 These two comments (Oct. 1) by two different attorneys in two different cases 
are the sort of thing that contribute to the low regard held by many people 
toward lawyers. 
</P>
<P>
 1.The defense attorney claimed that his client, given four life sentences for 
firing a gun into a crowd at the Westminster Mall, should have been charged 
with a lesser crime because the intent to kill was never proven. (What was the 
intent of firing a deadly weapon into a crowd -- fun and gaiety?) 
</P>
<P>
 2. The attorney for the woman charged with torturing a 10-year-old boy says 
all charges should be dismissed as the California statute on torture is vague 
and unconstitutional. (If what was reported in the news that has been done to 
the child had been inflicted on this attorney, would he have called it torture 
then?) 
</P>
<P>
 MARK TEMPLE 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach 
</P>
