<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOS ALAMITOS; FORMER JOCKEY PURSUES FIRST MAJOR AS A TRAINER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STACY PIGOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former jockey Danny Mitchell has a chance to win his first major stakes race 
as a trainer with The Money Crunch in tonight's $80,000 California Derby at Los 
Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
 The Money Crunch, a 3-year-old Tolltac filly, moved to the Mitchell stable in 
August and since has won three of four races and finished second in the 
Governor's Cup Derby. 
</P>
<P>
 Ridden by Joe Badilla, Jr., The Money Crunch ran 400 yards in 20.10 seconds in 
the derby trials Sept 23, easily winning the heat and qualifying fourth for the 
final. 
</P>
<P>
 The Money Crunch will have to overcome the inside post position in the final, 
where she will race champion 2-year-old filly and fastest qualifier Jumping Tac 
Flash, among others. STACY PIGOTT 
</P>
</TEXT>
