<P>
LOCAL NOTES: MATER DEI'S TICEHURST PLANS TO ATTEND USC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brad Ticehurst of Mater Dei made an oral commitment to USC, Mater Dei baseball 
Coach Bob Ickes said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ticehurst, a shortstop, was an All-Orange County selection by The Times and 
also an All-Southern Section Division I selection. In 27 games last season, 
Ticehurst hit .427 with six home runs, 23 runs batted in and 14 stolen bases. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Lynn Lovingier of Calvary Chapel made an oral commitment to play women's 
volleyball at Tennessee, said her mother, Jan.  
</P>
<P>
 Lovingier, a right-side hitter who has helped the Eagles earn a No. 10 ranking 
in the county, decided to attend Tennessee after visiting the campus last 
weekend. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
