<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL; SECODA LEADS VALENCIA PAST SUNNY HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON CLIFFORD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Valencia quarterback Joe Secoda played a part in every point Thursday night, 
leading the Tigers to an 18-6 nonleague football victory over Sunny Hills at 
Valencia High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Secoda threw for one score, ran for another, kicked a field goal and an extra 
point and ran in a two-point conversion.Secoda completed 12 of 17 passes for 
142 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Valencia defense dominated the Lancers (1-4) throughout the final three 
quarters. Sunny Hills quarterback Greg Garand completed 13 of 32 passes for 157 
yards, but four of his passes were intercepted. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers got on the board first, on their second possession of the game. 
Garand hit Eric Hernandez for a 12-yard touchdown, capping an eight-play, 
84-yard drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing 6-0, the Tigers (3-1-1) scored on their second possession of the 
second quarter when Secoda ran in from two yards out. His kick gave the Tigers 
a 7-6 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Secoda increased the Tigers' lead just before halftime by making a 27-yard 
field goal. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tigers' final score came with 2:13 left in the third quarter when Secoda 
hit Chris Roussin on a 14-yard score. Secoda then took the fumbled extra-point 
snap and ran in for the two-point conversion, giving the Tigers an 18-6 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia's Jermaine Gray had a game-high 103 yards in 21 carries. Chris 
Velotta had 54 yards in 12 carries for the Lancers. JON CLIFFORD 
</P>
</TEXT>
