<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL; YOUNG'S RUNNING LEADS FULLERTON PAST GLENN, 41-7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GABE LACQUES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chris Young rushed for 154 yards and two touchdowns as Fullerton beat Norwalk 
Glenn, 41-7, Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Young scored on runs of 31 and 14 yards, and had a touchdown run of 47 yards 
called back because of a clipping penalty. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton built its big lead early. Glenn quarterback James Young fumbled on 
the fourth play of the game, and Fullerton's Joseph Emigh recovered. 
</P>
<P>
 On the next play, Fullerton quarterback Gabe Almanza, who was making his first 
start of the season, connected with Jayson Garcia on a 40-yard touchdown pass 
for a 7-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 On Fullerton's first possession of the second quarter, Young capped a six-play 
drive with a 31-yard touchdown run. 
</P>
<P>
 Tyler Brickell gave Fullerton (3-2) a 20-0 halftime lead when he intercepted a 
pass by Young and returned it 27 yards for a touchdown with 1 minute 30 seconds 
left in the half. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton capped its scoring on a two-yard run by John Wilkie, Young's 14-yard 
run and a 61-yard punt return by Kyle Overby. 
</P>
<P>
 The Indians' defense shut out Glenn (1-3-1) until the 2:40 mark of the fourth 
quarter, when Chris Harris caught a 13-yard touchdown pass from Young. 
</P>
<P>
 Almanza completed nine of 12 passes for 131 yards and a touchdown. GABE 
LACQUES 
</P>
