<P>
PREP FOOTBALL; UNIVERSITY BEATS SADDLEBACK WITH HIGHFIELD'S HELP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A seven-yard touchdown run by Tucker Highfield in the first quarter helped 
University defeat Saddleback, 24-6, in a nonleague game Thursday night at the 
Santa Ana Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 Highfield led University (2-3) by rushing for 123 yards in 19 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Highfield's touchdown run, with seven minutes 11 seconds remaining in the 
first quarter, capped a 68-yard, seven-play drive. 
</P>
<P>
 University held Saddleback (1-4) to 98 yards total offense. 
</P>
<P>
 University extended its lead to 14-0 on a nine-yard touchdown run by Stuart 
Meurer with 2:27 remaining in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 In the second quarter, University's Stephen McKee sacked quarterback Brian 
Killingbeck, who fumbled. 
</P>
<P>
 Sepehr Sharifi recovered the ball and ran 54 yards for a touchdown to put 
University ahead, 21-0, with 28 left in the half. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback got on the scoreboard when Danny Verino ran 75 yards for a 
touchdown with 7:25 left in the third quarter, to cut University's lead to 
21-6. The kick failed. 
</P>
<P>
 But University countered on its next drive. Charles Thompson kicked a 25-yard 
field goal with four minutes remaining in the third quarter to put the Trojans 
ahead, 24-6. 
</P>
