<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; CORONA DEL MAR UPSETS IRVINE IN GIRLS' CROSS-COUNTRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Corona del Mar upset top-ranked Irvine (2-1) in girls' Sea View League 
cross-country, 23-32, Thursday at Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
 Tracey Clark took first place for the sixth-ranked Sea Kings, finishing in 18 
minutes 12 seconds. Brooke Meek (19:09) and Dresden Howell (19:30) finished 
third and fourth to help seal the victory for Corona del Mar (3-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine's Jessica Corbin, Orange County's top runner, has bronchitis and has 
been out all week. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Sea View League girls' cross-country: 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro 19, Woodbridge 44 -- Junior Stacy Roberson finished first for El Toro 
on the three-mile O'Neill Regional Park course in 19:54. El Toro improved to 
2-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 University 25, Laguna Beach 30 -- Sophomore Misha Wilson of University set a 
course record of 19:47, breaking the mark of 19:59 on the three-mile Eric Hulst 
Memorial Course in Laguna Beach. University is 2-0 in league. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 24, Marina 3 -- Fifth-ranked Edison (3-0) was led by second-place 
finisher Keri Wright, who ran three miles in 18:54. Heather Cuthbertson was 
first for Marina in 18:47. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden West League boys' cross-country: 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana 22, Saddleback 33 -- Second-ranked Santa Ana (4-0) out-sprinted 
eighth-ranked Saddleback (3-1). Danny Rivero led Santa Ana with a second-place 
finish (15:38) on Mason Park's three-mile course. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 27, Santa Margarita 28 -- Ninth-ranked Newport Harbor (2-1) 
edged Santa Margarita as the Sailors' Shahram DeZahd finished first (16:12) 
over three miles at Santa Margarita. 
</P>
<P>
 In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills 26, Capistrano Valley 32 -- Juan Almejo finished second (15:46) 
over three miles to lead Dana Hills (2-0). Aldaberto Sanchez of Capistrano 
Valley (1-1) finished first at 15:27. 
</P>
<P>
 In Sunset League boys' cross-country: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 20, Marina 35 -- Jeremy Milton won in 15:56 over three miles for host 
Edison (4-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In Sea View League girls' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 14, Santa Margarita 4 -- Nina Vaughan swept her sets, 7-5, 6-2, 
6-3, to lead the eighth-ranked Sea Kings (7-3-1, 3-0) over No. 9 Santa 
Margarita. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 12, Woodbridge 6 -- Vanessa Godbey swept her sets at No. 1 
singles, 7-6 (7-3), 6-2, 6-0, to lead No. 2 Newport Harbor over the 
third-ranked Warriors.  
</P>
