<HEADLINE>
<P>
A LITTLE BIT OF HISTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jeff Nelson of Burbank High set a national high school record of 8 minutes 
36.3 seconds in the two-mile run at the 1979 Pepsi Invitational track and field 
meet. 
</P>
<P>
 Nelson broke the mark of 8:40.9, set by Craig Virgin of Lebanon, Ill., in 
1973. 
</P>
