<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: COMPANY TOWN; DISNEY MARKETING EXECUTIVE TO WEAR SENIOR VP 
EARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Film marketing executive Robert B. Levin is moving over to senior vice 
president of corporate marketing and communications at Walt Disney Co. 
</P>
<P>
 Levin has been president of Buena Vista Pictures Marketing, overseeing 
worldwide marketing of motion pictures released by Walt Disney, Touchstone and 
Hollywood pictures, and also for Disney's "Beauty and the Beast" production on 
Broadway. 
</P>
<P>
 Dick Cook, Buena Vista's distribution chief, is expected to also assume 
responsibility for marketing, sources say. 
</P>
<P>
 Twentieth Century Fox named Alex Gartner senior vice president for its new 
mainstream film production division, headed by producer Laura Ziskin. 
</P>
<P>
 Also named as vice presidents of production were Sandy Isaac and Leslie 
Morgan, both of whom worked at Ziskin's production company before she was hired 
by Fox. 
</P>
<P>
 Separately, Fox named production executive Christopher Meledandri president of 
its new family films division. 
</P>
<P>
 Longtime music publicist Paula Batson has resigned her position as senior vice 
president of public relations and special production development at MCA Music 
Entertainment Group. 
</P>
<P>
 Sony Pictures Entertainment said Burt Berman has been hired as executive vice 
president of music for Columbia TriStar Motion Picture Cos. 
</P>
<P>
 James L. English was named president of Playboy networks worldwide.  
</P>
<P>
 Kathryn Cohen has been promoted to general manager of Prime Ticket Network. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ellen Rubin is the new vice president of public relations for QVC Inc., the 
home shopping network. 
</P>
<P>
 FX Networks appointed Carol Sussman director of programming. 
</P>
<P>
 * Kristine Belson was named vice president of production for Turner Pictures 
Worldwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
