<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE TIMES MUSIC INDEX: COMPANY TOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 STACKING UP SALES 
</P>
<P>
 Total album and single sales of CDs and cassettes for the week ended Oct. 2, 
compared to week-ago and year-ago levels, in millions of units sold:  
</P>
<P>
 Latest week: Albums: 10.6 Singles: 1.8 
</P>
<P>
 Week-ago: Albums: 9.7 Singles: 1.7 
</P>
<P>
 Year-ago: Albums: 9.4 Singles: 2.0 Hits Magazine Tip of the Week 
</P>
<P>
 Questions are being raised about whether Michael Jackson's much-anticipated 
greatest-hits package with several new tracks will be in stores in time to 
capture holiday shopping dollars. Jackson is supposed to have already delivered 
the project to Epic Records, but frustrated insiders say he is not fully 
satisfied with every aspect of the package. There is speculation about whether 
Epic will release the project in the first quarter of 1995 or reschedule it for 
later in the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
