<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: PLACENTIA; HERITAGE FESTIVAL WILL BEGIN TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city will celebrate its history with entertainment and family events at 
the 30th annual Heritage Festival tonight and Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The festivities begin at 7:30 tonight with a Casino Night at the Placentia 
Round Table Women's Club, 901 N. Bradford Ave.For $25 per person or $40 per 
couple, those attending receive $200 in gambling scrip to use at blackjack, 
roulette and craps tables, with proceeds going to Rotary Club college 
scholarships. 
</P>
<P>
 The festival, themed "Placentia -- The Dream Is Alive," continues at 7 a.m. 
Saturday with a pancake breakfast at Kraemer Memorial Park, Chapman and 
Bradford avenues. The Chamber of Commerce will host the event, which begins at 
7 a.m. and has a $3 admission charge. 
</P>
<P>
 The park is also a good vantage point for the Heritage Parade, which begins at 
10 a.m. at Kraemer and Madison avenues and wends its way past the park. At 
Bradford Park, festival events will be held from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
