<P>
BRIEFLY: HEALTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wyle Labs to Sell Scientific Services Unit: William E. Simon & Sons Inc. said 
it is leading a group of investors that signed a definitive agreement to 
acquire Wyle Laboratories' Scientific Services & Systems division for $30 
million in cash.The group includes F. Stephen Wyle, the son of the founder of 
Irvine-based Wyle Laboratories, and some members of the division's senior 
management. They expect to complete the acquisition in three months. Scientific 
Services & Systems is a research, engineering, testing and support services 
company whose customers are in aerospace, defense and energy. 
</P>
