<P>
 Wyle Laboratories: The company said Thursday that it has signed an agreement 
to sell its Scientific Services & Systems division for $30 million to a group 
of investors led by William E. Simon & Sons Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 The Irvine company said it agreed to sell its division to the Los 
Angeles-based merchant bank so that it can focus on its core business of 
distributing semiconductors and computer products to the electronics industry. 
</P>
<P>
 F. Stephen Wyle, son of the founder of Wyle Laboratories, will become chief 
executive officer of the newly formed private company. William E. Simon & Sons 
will have about an 80% stake in the company and will have representation on the 
board of directors. 
</P>
<P>
 The deal is expected to close within 90 days. 
