$15 in change. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, the victim's family vowed at a news conference Thursday to continue 
their efforts to help find the two men who killed Randy Terrian, 37. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've got to catch these people," said Archie Terrian, 60, of northern San 
Diego County, his voice breaking as he spoke of the murder of his son Sept. 24. 
"We watch the TV news every night and all it is is murders and robberies up 
here. . . . Something's got to be done." 
</P>
<P>
